article.headline: Massachusetts 53, Saint Louis 50
article.story: AMHERST, Mass. (AP) -- James Life and Gary Forbes made a pair of free throws each in the final seconds to lift Massachusetts to a 53-50 victory over Saint Louis in Atlantic 10 Conference action Saturday. The victory kept the Minutemen (21-7, 11-3 A-10) in a tie with Xavier for the league lead. Forbes, with 13 points, was the only double-figure scorer for UMass. The Minutemen shot a lowly 29.5 from the field for the game. Ian Vouyoukas had a game-high 18 points for Saint Louis (17-10, 7-6). His hooking layup put St. Louis ahead, 50-49, with 25 seconds to play. But Life then drew a foul on a drive and made the two shots from the line that put UMass on top for good. After the Billikens missed on the other end, Forbes made his final two foul shots just before the buzzer. The game was tied four times in the defensive-minded first half, with Forbes making a runner to give UMass a 22-20 lead at halftime. St. Louis' 17-13 lead was the largest gap between the two teams before intermission.
